Make the turbojpeg ExternalProject_Add safe to re-run.

CMake's ExternalProject_Add re-runs a `git fetch` + `git rev-parse HEAD`
update step on every build. If the .git directory inside the cached
checkout is stripped (e.g. by CI cache layers that ignore nested git
repos), the update step fails with:

  Failed to get the hash for HEAD:
  fatal: not a git repository: '.git'

...which breaks every incremental rebuild. Adding UPDATE_DISCONNECTED
TRUE makes cmake skip the update step after the initial clone, and
GIT_SHALLOW TRUE avoids fetching the full libjpeg-turbo history when
we only want a pinned tag.

This only applies when UHDR_BUILD_DEPS=ON (the `vendored` feature). With
system libjpeg found, ExternalProject_Add is never called in the first
place.

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -480,6 +480,8 @@ if(NOT JPEG_FOUND)
     ExternalProject_Add(${JPEGTURBO_TARGET_NAME}
         GIT_REPOSITORY https://github.com/libjpeg-turbo/libjpeg-turbo.git
         GIT_TAG 3.1.0
+        GIT_SHALLOW TRUE
+        UPDATE_DISCONNECTED TRUE
         PREFIX ${JPEGTURBO_PREFIX_DIR}
         SOURCE_DIR ${JPEGTURBO_SOURCE_DIR}
         BINARY_DIR ${JPEGTURBO_BINARY_DIR}
@@ -497,6 +499,8 @@ if(NOT JPEG_FOUND)
     ExternalProject_Add(${JPEGTURBO_TARGET_NAME}
         GIT_REPOSITORY https://github.com/libjpeg-turbo/libjpeg-turbo.git
         GIT_TAG 3.1.0
+        GIT_SHALLOW TRUE
+        UPDATE_DISCONNECTED TRUE
         PREFIX ${JPEGTURBO_PREFIX_DIR}
         SOURCE_DIR ${JPEGTURBO_SOURCE_DIR}
         BINARY_DIR ${JPEGTURBO_BINARY_DIR}
